Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:15.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the beginning of the Paleozoic era, the Cambrian explosion occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:17.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a large number of organisms made their appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.03,0:02:18.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, at the end of the Paleozoic era,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:20.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,the world changed to an infinite spread of 2 tatami,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.11,0:02:20.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(190,180)\t(0,190,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(1000,1200,\c&H000000&)}2 Tatami Age\N (Permian Period)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:24.20,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and in the beginning of the Mesozoic era it \Nincreased by one as the "3 Tatami Age" arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.62,0:02:23.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(180,170)\t(0,180,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(1000,1200,\c&H000000&)}3 Tatami Age
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.20,0:02:26.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as the dinosaurs appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.33,0:02:28.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,the laid out tatami were completely stomped into nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.58,0:02:30.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and time moved on to the Jurassic Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.12,0:02:30.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(180,170)\t(0,180,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(1000,1200,\c&H000000&)}Jurassic Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:32.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(180,170)\t(0,180,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(1000,1200,\c&H000000&)}Cretaceous Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.79,0:02:33.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that came the majestic glory of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.34,0:02:33.54,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(180,180)\t(0,180,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(1000,1200,\c&H000000&)}Tertiary Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:35.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And before long, in the present world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.38,0:02:35.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(180,170)\t(0,180,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(1000,1200,\c&H000000&)}Quaternary Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:36.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,as the bell tolls for the end of the quaternary part of the Cenozoic period,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:38.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,once again tatami have been spread across the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:39.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,marking the beginning of the "4.5 Tatami Age."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.13,0:02:40.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8\bord2.007435\fs110.408922\be1\c&H000000&\fnFootlight MT Light\fad(180,0)\t(0,180,\c&HFCFCFC&)\t(750,1700,\c&H000000&)}4.5 Tatami Age
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.51,0:02:45.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going back in time is quite unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:46.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, I was wandering, lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:50.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,in an unbelievable world of infinitely many 4.5 tatami rooms laid side by side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:52.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had already been 2 months since I began wandering.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.86,0:02:58.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I figured this world had no end, I continued my pitiful, endless march.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.86,0:03:00.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If I open the door, there is the hallway."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.53,0:03:03.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would be an astronomical miraculous, and fortuitous happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:06.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the rooms looked the same, \Nbut they all had slight differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:09.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Each one was inhabited by a slightly different me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.25,0:03:13.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, all of them seemed to have led some gloriously wasted campus life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.88,0:03:18.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tried to begin studying each one, \Nand myself as a whole,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.09,0:03:19.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I immediately lost my motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.34,0:03:20.76,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and instead my interest shifted
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:23.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the traces in each room of the \Nvarious people I was mixed up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.89,0:03:28.02,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person named Aijima was one year older \Nthan me and the head of the Library Committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:30.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a small man who would not allow you to check out more than 2 books at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.43,0:03:32.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you could see in his eyes through those \Nglasses that his polite face masked hypocrisy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.23,0:03:34.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I got an impression that he was insufferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.15,0:03:36.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall seeing something of a purge in some Secret Society he was in charge of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.86,0:03:39.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,after someone entrapped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.90,0:03:43.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.28,0:03:49.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know a Higuchi who lives on the second floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.16,0:03:50.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.62,0:03:54.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. We are collecting information on this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:58.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy has caused everyone quite a lot of trouble, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.59,0:04:01.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's like some youkai with no redeemable aspect at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.92,0:04:04.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The two that came calling had their faces covered,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:07.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but that vocal tick had to have been Aijima.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:11.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm going to tell you a number of things.\N If anything comes to mind, answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.27,0:04:16.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Airship. Gozan. Honwaka. Kohinata.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:21.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kohinata-san was the poster child of a raven-haired maiden on campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:23.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I were ever perchance to meet her,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.40,0:04:24.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet I would lavish her with gifts without a second thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:27.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,regardless of the hardship on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.03,0:04:32.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,With their word association game not bearing any fruit, the two left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.16,0:04:36.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That dental hygienist Hanuki-san was also an alumni of my university.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.17,0:04:39.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I know that the two of them were in the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:41.84,dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I'm mentioning it, that cart owner also seems to be from the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:43.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a small world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.34,0:04:46.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Higuchi was an eighth year student on the brink,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:49.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he was fixed in his ways and took things at \Nhis own pace, although he had a stately manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.18,0:04:52.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hanuki-san would frequently \Nvisit him at the boarding house,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:54.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and it seems like he took on a couple of apprentices.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.60,0:04:56.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was he so revered?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.60,0:04:59.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,His extremely useless life, \Nhis propensity for fierce self-effacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.23,0:05:01.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it was all lined with deep learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:07.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,In one of my lives, I had become his disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:09.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man whose entire body seemed chiseled out of stone, Mr. Jougasaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:10.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\p1\bord0\be2\c&HDADFF2&\pos(169.352818,92.342007)}m 1447 254 l 1426 309 1451 339 1735 345 1759 287 1737 260 1589 254
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:10.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\be3\bord0\fs110.408922\fnVeteran Typewriter\c&H050607&\pos(1598.329854,358.327138)}Glue
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:13.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,seemed to have taken over some war of pranks with Mr. Higuchi.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.41,0:05:15.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't look like that sort of person at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:15.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\p1\bord0\be2\c&HA6B4E1&\pos(94.196242,234.869888)}m 120 756 l 126 861 292 991 308 921
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:15.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\be2\fscy130\fs80.297398\fax0.6\c&H131C3D&\b0\frx336\fry320\frz311.837\fnDoctor Soos Bold\pos(159.331942,902.342007)}Pepper
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:18.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he succeeded as the next proxy, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:23.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Mr. Jougasaki had a lover named Kaori-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:25.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,he seemed to have some interest in Hanuki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:28.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hanuki-san seemed to both be dating Mr. Higuchi and not dating him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.34,0:05:31.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and anyway Mr. Higuchi said that he \Nwas going on a trip around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.18,0:05:33.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you come with me, Hanuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.22,0:05:35.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can speak English, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.52,0:05:37.69,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be crazy. This is foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:39.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Higuchi had feelings for Hanuki-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and yet he was going to leave her...\N How frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.44,0:05:45.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it was like he was pretending not to \Nnotice the diamond dropped on the roadside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.57,0:05:50.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at it like this, humans really are deep; \Nthey have many faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:54.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a huge shame to scorn people just because of a single hasty look at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.45,0:05:57.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look at them from all angles, \Nyou'll be able to see new, hidden sides to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:06:00.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will put everything that I've been up on this shelf,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.63,0:06:02.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and once having put it all aside, \NI won't dare to take it down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.96,0:06:05.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, I should have been \Nsatisfied to the point of bursting
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:08.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,by all these different people \Nsurrounding my campus lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:10.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What in the world was I doing?
Dialogue: 1,0:06:10.22,0:06:13.47,dialogue,,0,0,50,,I knew not how to partake of the world.
